DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260402
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260403
SUMMARY:Ekphrasis: A PCC District-Wide Faculty Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Exhibition Dates: February 26\, 2026 â€“ April 17\, 2026Galle
 ry hours: Monday â€“ Friday\, 8am-4pm.Opening Reception: Saturday\, Febru
 ary 28\, 5:00 â€“ 8:00 p.m.Additional Events announced soon.Ekphrasis com
 es from the Greek words ek (out) and phrĂˇsis (speak)\, literally speakin
 g out. The Poetry Foundation defines an ekphrastic poem as a vivid descri
 ption of a work of art. But ekphrasis is more than giving voice to the vi
 sual\, more than mere description. Ekphrasis offers one's voice in dialog
 ue with another. In Ekphrasis: A PCC Faculty Exhibition\, recent art from
  Portland Community College art faculty and lab techs is positioned in co
 nversation\, both with each other and with writing faculty who composed e
 kphrastic poems about the work.â€”Event Details: https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp
 ?id=382395 (https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382395)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:Exhibition Dates: February 26\, 2026 â€“ Apr
 il 17\, 2026<br />Gallery hours: Monday â€“ Friday\, 8am-4pm.<br />Openin
 g Reception: Saturday\, February 28\, 5:00 â€“ 8:00 p.m.<br />Additional 
 Events announced soon.<br />Ekphrasis comes from the Greek words ek (out)
  and phrĂˇsis (speak)\, literally speaking out. The Poetry Foundation def
 ines an ekphrastic poem as a vivid description of a work of art. But ekph
 rasis is more than giving voice to the visual\, more than mere descriptio
 n. Ekphrasis offers one's voice in dialogue with another. In Ekphrasis: A
  PCC Faculty Exhibition\, recent art from Portland Community College art 
 faculty and lab techs is positioned in conversation\, both with each othe
 r and with writing faculty who composed ekphrastic poems about the work.<
 br />â€”<br />Event Details: <a href="https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382395"
  target="_blank">https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382395</a>
