SUMMARY:Every-Body Moves
DESCRIPTION:A weekly event to create a safe space for people of any size 
 and ability to come and talk about their relationship to exercise/movemen
 t- no pressure to do any exercise if you're not interested. Maybe you jus
 t want to do some breathing\, or talk about mobility in general\, or you 
 want someone to listen to your concerns about trying to stay active and g
 et aroundâ€¦. we're here for you.If you want to do some movement\, we als
 o to have space to do light body movements and share ideas/exercises with
  each other- yoga\, stretching\, calisthenics\, tai-chi\, whatever you're
  into!The Accessibility Hub is a weight-neutral space that centers disabi
 lity and those of disabled experience- however\, all students\, staff\, f
 aculty and community members are welcome.â€”Event Details: https://hub.pc
 c.edu/rsvp?id=382238 (https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382238)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:A weekly event to create a safe space for pe
 ople of any size and ability to come and talk about their relationship to
  exercise/movement- no pressure to do any exercise if you're not interest
 ed. Maybe you just want to do some breathing\, or talk about mobility in 
 general\, or you want someone to listen to your concerns about trying to 
 stay active and get aroundâ€¦. we're here for you.<br />If you want to do
  some movement\, we also to have space to do light body movements and sha
 re ideas/exercises with each other- yoga\, stretching\, calisthenics\, ta
 i-chi\, whatever you're into!<br />The Accessibility Hub is a weight-neut
 ral space that centers disability and those of disabled experience- howev
 er\, all students\, staff\, faculty and community members are welcome.<br
  />â€”<br />Event Details: <a href="https://hub.pcc.edu/rsvp?id=382238" t
